{% set inlineFormStyles %}.inline-form {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--size-s);
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.inline-form input {
  flex: 1;
  min-width: 200px;
}{% endset %}

{% set ghostButtonStyles %}.cta-with-bg .button.ghost {
  color: var(--color-white);
  border-color: var(--color-white);
}

.cta-with-bg .button.ghost:hover {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
}{% endset %}

{% set ctaBackgroundStyles %}.cta-with-bg {
  background-image: url('/images/cta-bg.jpg');
  background-size: cover;
  background-position: center;
  position: relative;
}

.cta-with-bg::before {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background: var(--color-overlay-strong);
}

.cta-with-bg > * {
  position: relative;
  color: var(--color-white);
}{% endset %}

<section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Call to Action (CTA) sections are critical conversion points on marketing pages. They typically appear after feature sections or at the bottom of landing pages, prompting users to take the next step. These patterns use <code>data-layout="cover"</code> for vertical centering and <code>data-layout="center"</code> for horizontal alignment.</p>
      <p><strong>Key features:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Vertical centering with <code>data-layout="cover"</code></li>
        <li>Multiple layout variants (centered, split, full-width)</li>
        <li>Background image support with overlays</li>
        <li>Inline form integration for lead capture</li>
        <li>Button groups with <code>data-layout="cluster"</code></li>
        <li>Responsive without media queries</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Centered CTA</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>The most common CTA pattern: centered headline, supporting text, and action buttons. Perfect for page endings and conversion sections.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/cta-centered.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/cta-centered"
      title="Centered CTA"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="Centered CTA with button group">&lt;section class="cta" data-layout="cover" data-layout-min="50vh" data-layout-padding="xl"&gt;
  &lt;div class="cta-content" data-layout="center" data-layout-max="normal" data-layout-gap="l"&gt;
    &lt;h2&gt;Ready to get started?&lt;/h2&gt;
    &lt;p class="lead"&gt;
      Join thousands of developers building better interfaces with Vanilla Breeze.
      Start your free trial today, no credit card required.
    &lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;nav&gt;
      &lt;ul data-layout="cluster" data-layout-justify="center" data-layout-gap="m"&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/signup/" class="button large"&gt;Start Free Trial&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/contact/" class="button large secondary"&gt;Talk to Sales&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/nav&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Split CTA with Form</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Text on one side, form or image on the other. Uses <code>data-layout="sidebar"</code> for a flexible two-column layout that stacks on narrow viewports. Great for newsletter signups and lead capture.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/cta-split.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/cta-split"
      title="Split CTA"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="Split CTA with inline form">&lt;section class="cta" data-layout="cover" data-layout-min="50vh" data-layout-padding="xl"&gt;
  &lt;div data-layout="center" data-layout-max="wide"&gt;
    &lt;div data-layout="sidebar" data-layout-gap="2xl" data-layout-sidebar-width="wide" data-layout-content-min="50"&gt;
      &lt;div data-layout="stack" data-layout-gap="l"&gt;
        &lt;h2&gt;Get notified when we launch&lt;/h2&gt;
        &lt;p class="lead"&gt;
          Be the first to know when new features are released.
          Sign up for early access and exclusive updates.
        &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;form class="inline-form" action="/subscribe" method="POST"&gt;
          &lt;form-field&gt;
            &lt;input type="email" name="email" required autocomplete="email" placeholder="Enter your email" aria-label="Email address" /&gt;
          &lt;/form-field&gt;
          &lt;button type="submit"&gt;Notify Me&lt;/button&gt;
        &lt;/form&gt;
        &lt;p class="text-sm text-muted"&gt;
          We respect your privacy. Unsubscribe at any time.
        &lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;img
        src="/images/cta-illustration.png"
        alt="Product illustration"
        width="500"
        height="375"
        loading="lazy"
      /&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;</code-block>

